[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":330},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2024\u002F07\u002F15\u002Fzero-width-space-zwsp-invisible-characters-that-break-code\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2024\u002F07\u002F15\u002Fzero-width-space-zwsp-invisible-characters-that-break-code\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2024\u002F07\u002F15\u002Fzero-width-space-zwsp-invisible-characters-that-break-code\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2024\u002F07\u002F15\u002Fzero-width-space-zwsp-invisible-characters-that-break-code\u002F":305,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2024\u002F07\u002F15\u002Fzero-width-space-zwsp-invisible-characters-that-break-code\u002F":314},"\u002Fother\u002F20240715\u002F604545734\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":285,"date":286,"description":287,"extension":288,"lang":289,"meta":290,"navigation":291,"path":292,"readingMinutes":293,"seo":294,"standalone":295,"stem":296,"tags":297,"tldr":302,"updated":286,"url":303,"__hash__":304},"content\u002Fen\u002FMisc\u002Fzero-width-space-zwsp-invisible-characters-that-break-code.md","Zero-Width Space (ZWSP): The Invisible Character That Breaks Your Code","8423095617",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":272},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,32,35,45,48,65,68,77,80,87,90,96,102,106,109,114,120,126,129,135,141,145,157,163,166,172,181,185,192,201,205,216,221,225,231,234,245,251,262,268],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Ever had this happen — the string on your screen reads just \"ABC\" or \"123\", but the code won't run or the URL won't post? Chances are you're staring at a \"ghost character\". This post covers one of the most common culprits — the zero-width space — and how to actually find it.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"zero-width-space-zwsp","Zero-Width Space (ZWSP)",[17,25,26,27,31],{},"Zero-width space, also called the non-printing space or zero-width blank — a bit of a mouthful. Easier framing: it's an ",[28,29,30],"strong",{},"invisible space character",".",[17,33,34],{},"What can it break?",[36,37,38,42],"ul",{},[39,40,41],"li",{},"URLs that won't actually fire",[39,43,44],{},"Code that won't run",[17,46,47],{},"Here's an example — an API URL with five zero-width spaces in it:",[49,50,55],"pre",{"className":51,"code":52,"language":53,"meta":54,"style":54},"language-txt shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","https:\u002F\u002Fexample.io​\u002Fv2​\u002Fapi​\u002Fhexschool​\u002Fproducts​\u002Fall\n","txt","",[56,57,58],"code",{"__ignoreMap":54},[59,60,63],"span",{"class":61,"line":62},"line",1,[59,64,52],{},[17,66,67],{},"And the cleaned-up version with the zero-width spaces removed:",[49,69,71],{"className":51,"code":70,"language":53,"meta":54,"style":54},"https:\u002F\u002Fexample.io\u002Fv2\u002Fapi\u002Fhexschool\u002Fproducts\u002Fall\n",[56,72,73],{"__ignoreMap":54},[59,74,75],{"class":61,"line":62},[59,76,70],{},[17,78,79],{},"To your eyes, and even pasted into VSCode, the two look identical.",[17,81,82],{},[83,84],"img",{"alt":85,"src":86},"ZWSP looks identical in VSCode","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fzwsp\u002Fcode.png",[17,88,89],{},"So you'd assume they're the same URL.",[17,91,92],{},[83,93],{"alt":94,"src":95},"Surely this is just a normal URL?","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fzwsp\u002F1721033403511.png",[17,97,98,99,31],{},"But this tiny invisible difference breaks the code. That's the zero-width space. It's not a bug — it's a real Unicode character: ",[56,100,101],{},"U+200B",[12,103,105],{"id":104},"how-to-find-and-remove-them","How to find and remove them",[17,107,108],{},"Copying the code above into VSCode won't show you the difference. So here are a few ways to actually catch these things.",[110,111,113],"h3",{"id":112},"invisible-characters","Invisible Characters",[17,115,116,117,119],{},"Open VSCode settings, search for ",[56,118,113],{},", and tick it. Now you can see the invisible whitespace.",[17,121,122],{},[83,123],{"alt":124,"src":125},"Invisible Characters setting in VSCode","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fzwsp\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202024-07-15%2017.11.55.png",[17,127,128],{},"Before and after comparison:",[17,130,131],{},[83,132],{"alt":133,"src":134},"Before","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fzwsp\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202024-07-15%2017.13.00.png",[17,136,137],{},[83,138],{"alt":139,"src":140},"After","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fzwsp\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202024-07-15%2017.13.48.png",[110,142,144],{"id":143},"non-basic-ascii","Non Basic ASCII",[17,146,147,148,150,151,153,154,31],{},"If turning on ",[56,149,113],{}," doesn't catch it, there's another option — open VSCode settings, search for ",[56,152,144],{},", and set it to ",[56,155,156],{},"true",[17,158,159],{},[83,160],{"alt":161,"src":162},"Non Basic ASCII setting","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fzwsp\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202024-07-15%2016.27.48.png",[17,164,165],{},"VSCode will now highlight anything that isn't basic ASCII — and the zero-width spaces in your URL show up clearly.",[17,167,168],{},[83,169],{"alt":170,"src":171},"Non Basic ASCII highlighting ZWSP","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fzwsp\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96_2024-07-15_16_29_22.jpg",[173,174,175],"blockquote",{},[17,176,177,180],{},[28,178,179],{},"Note","\nASCII is a character encoding covering English letters, digits, and punctuation. Chinese, Japanese, Korean — all outside ASCII. Zero-width space is also outside ASCII, which is why \"Non Basic ASCII\" catches it.",[110,182,184],{"id":183},"paste-into-the-browser","Paste into the browser",[17,186,187,188,191],{},"Another trick — paste the URL into a browser's address bar. The browser URL-encodes the zero-width space into ",[56,189,190],{},"%E2%80%8B",", so you'll suddenly see them everywhere:",[49,193,195],{"className":51,"code":194,"language":53,"meta":54,"style":54},"https:\u002F\u002Fexample.io\u002Fv2%E2%80%8B\u002Fapi%E2%80%8B\u002Fhexschool%E2%80%8B\u002Fproducts%E2%80%8B\u002Fall\n",[56,196,197],{"__ignoreMap":54},[59,198,199],{"class":61,"line":62},[59,200,194],{},[110,202,204],{"id":203},"gremlins-extension","Gremlins extension",[17,206,207,208,215],{},"I'd recommend installing the ",[209,210,214],"a",{"href":211,"rel":212},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=nhoizey.gremlins",[213],"nofollow","Gremlins"," VSCode extension. It surfaces invisible whitespace and a bunch of other \"gotcha\" characters, so you can locate the problem fast.",[17,217,218],{},[83,219],{"alt":204,"src":220},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fzwsp\u002F%E7%A5%9E%E7%A7%98%E7%AC%A6%E8%99%9F-Zero-width-space-ZWSP%EF%BC%88%E7%9C%8B%E4%B8%8D%E8%A6%8B%E7%9A%84%E7%A9%BA%E7%99%BD%EF%BC%89_md_%E2%80%94_isRayNotArray.jpg",[12,222,224],{"id":223},"closing-thoughts","Closing thoughts",[17,226,227],{},[83,228],{"alt":229,"src":230},"After spending a day debugging only to realize it was ZWSP","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fzwsp\u002F1721033222323.png",[17,232,233],{},"You can technically use this trick to mess with a coworker — but please don't. xD",[17,235,236,237,240,241,244],{},"For completeness, here's how you'd type one. On Mac, hit ",[56,238,239],{},"Control + Command + Space"," to open the emoji picker, search ",[56,242,243],{},"ZERO WIDTH SPACE",", and you'll find it.",[17,246,247],{},[83,248],{"alt":249,"src":250},"ZERO WIDTH SPACE in macOS emoji picker","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fzwsp\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202024-07-15%2016.56.15.png",[17,252,253,254,257,258,261],{},"On Windows — hold ",[56,255,256],{},"Alt"," and type ",[56,259,260],{},"8203"," on the numpad to produce one.",[17,263,264,265],{},"Again — please don't use this to prank anyone. ",[266,267],"d",{},[269,270,271],"style",{},"html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}",{"title":54,"searchDepth":273,"depth":273,"links":274},2,[275,276,277,284],{"id":14,"depth":273,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":273,"text":23},{"id":104,"depth":273,"text":105,"children":278},[279,281,282,283],{"id":112,"depth":280,"text":113},3,{"id":143,"depth":280,"text":144},{"id":183,"depth":280,"text":184},{"id":203,"depth":280,"text":204},{"id":223,"depth":273,"text":224},"Misc","2024-07-15 15:26:17","Ever had a string that looks like plain \"ABC\" or \"123\" on screen but won't run as code or won't post as a URL? That's often a \"ghost character\" — specifically the zero-width space. This post covers what zero-width space (ZWSP) is, why it sneaks into your code, and how to find and remove it before it eats your afternoon.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002Fzero-width-space-zwsp-invisible-characters-that-break-code","2",{"title":6,"description":287},false,"en\u002FMisc\u002Fzero-width-space-zwsp-invisible-characters-that-break-code",[298,299,300,301],"Troubleshooting","Zero-width-space","Encoding","Unicode",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2024\u002F07\u002F15\u002Fzero-width-space-zwsp-invisible-characters-that-break-code\u002F","_cZGPiKL6TF03Ynlf27TSqpubgsOWh0jWOGM4-duPYk",{"newer":306,"older":310},{"url":307,"title":308,"date":309},"\u002Fen\u002Flearning\u002F2024\u002F07\u002F15\u002Fwhy-am-i-the-coach-again-2024-nodejs-program\u002F","Why Am I a Coach Again for the 2024 Node.js Enterprise Capstone Program?!","2024-07-15 19:03:59",{"url":311,"title":312,"date":313},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2024\u002F05\u002F14\u002Fjavascript-filter-falsy-values-tricks\u002F","A Few Filter Tricks: Drop All the Falsy Values in One Line","2024-05-14 14:34:31",[315,320,325],{"url":316,"title":317,"date":318,"readingMinutes":319},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F06\u002F23\u002Fmac-stats-menu-bar-system-monitor\u002F","Stats — The Free Open-Source macOS Menu Bar System Monitor I Use Every Day (CPU, GPU, Temperature, Network)","2026-06-23 10:00:00","5",{"url":321,"title":322,"date":323,"readingMinutes":324},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F26\u002Fhow-much-does-a-blog-really-earn-with-google-adsense\u002F","Can a Blog Really Make Tens of Thousands of Dollars a Month? Real Google AdSense Numbers, Explained","2026-05-26 21:00:00","6",{"url":326,"title":327,"date":328,"readingMinutes":329},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F18\u002Fvscode-disable-integrated-browser-auto-open\u002F","VSCode Opens Every Link in the Integrated Browser? How to Disable Auto Takeover","2026-05-18 14:30:00","4",1784020370354]